üí™ Hello friends! I wanted to share something that has really helped me during my yoga practices: sometimes for me, many powerful emotions surface during practice that can be overwhelming to deal with. I¬†have a tendency¬†to get so into my own head and judge myself (like I did when I had difficulty doing the asanas last month) that I just want to quit¬†and disappear because I feel so icky and unworthy; it's almost like I don't want people to see me in this vulnerable and human state. But I realize that I need to own my feelings and be accountable for myself to and my feelings.

Today, one of my friends invited me to join her and her husband to read Christmas stories to kids at a coffee shop, and it was really cool to just hang out with them and be silly with the kids. It turned into a¬†nice good vibe sesh that was much needed, and so many hours passed by quickly. The biggest difference I noticed¬†during this hang¬†out¬†versus previous ones was my heart chakra:¬†it felt like a furnace of intense Leo fire that was coursing through my center! I could literally feel the prana flowing, and "fire" coursing through my heart center¬†(especially with the recent practices). I¬†also felt¬†that my connection to my friends¬†was a lot stronger, because the connection to myself is stronger. 

It also feels kinda crazy that this rebirth of my fire energy happened on a Winter Solstice, which I think is symbolic for the Sun's rebirth and renewal? I'm not sure entirely, but the synchronicity is just so insane. By the time I got home and rolled out the yoga mat, I layed down on it and just KO-ed from¬†all the interaction today; it's ironic that going out helps me process energy released from mat practice, but mat practice helps me ground out energy absorbed from¬†being out with people. Maybe this will change as I continue to grow as a person. But fortunately for¬†home practice,¬†I¬†can attend even if¬†it's¬†2AM. Baha!

Today was intense in good ways, and this journey can be difficult but enlightening. I'm grateful for you, and grateful for renewal. I am secure within my skin. Namaste üôè

Well I have to admit it took me a while today to seize the affirmation...
‚ÄúI am secure‚Äù
Am I ?
‚ÄúI feel secure‚Äù
Do I ?
Is not that I don‚Äôt want, but I don‚Äôt tend to. Consciously I want to, but sub-consciously I‚Äôm more (or I used to be more) the kind of person that freak out about things and how they could go wrong, being anxious about what will be, always thinking about the ‚Äúwhat if‚Äù...
And then your calm, the practice, the safe environment, breathing deep inside, the sun rising, everything became clear, such an epiphany...
How much time have I spent worrying about things and how they could get wrong anytime rather then enjoying the ride???
How could I be that person???
‚ÄúEveryone down to extended child pose‚Äù, you said.
And there I am: a child again.
And children feel secure, they are secure, because we parents are there for them to be secure.
What changes in adult life? Or better, why things should change in adult life?
I want my children to feel secure, to be secure, and for that I have to be secure myself.
And I have not a single one acceptable reason not to be secure.
So it‚Äôs now 11 hours past the daily mat, and I eventually seized my mantra.
‚ÄúI can be secure‚Äù
And it will feel good
Namaste üôè
